== Overview ==
Harimizu Utaki enshrines the two deities, Koi-tsuno (古意角) and Koitama (姑依玉). It has been a site of worship since before the establishment of the [[Ryukyu Kingdom]] (1429) and is the setting for various [[myths]] and [[legends]] related to the creation of Miyako Island<ref name="okinawastory" />.

