According to "Chūdō-shi Honke Puku," the stone walls on the southern side were built by [[Nakasone Toyomiya]] after his victory over [[Oyake Akahachi]] in the [[1500 Oyake Akahachi Rebellion]], fulfilling his vow to enshrine the spirits that aided his success<ref name="shiseki">[http://www.city.miyakojima.lg.jp/kanko/bunkazai/miyakojimabunkazai/shiseki.html Historic Sites 1-25] Miyakojima City</ref>.

